node.text: So dark up top in the woods 😳The weather has finally cleared up a little and was able to do some training at the local on my DH bike for the first time in ages! 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 extremely fortunate to be allowed to carry on training during this time.

node.text:
Lenzerheide World Cup iPhone photo dump ✨ You guys liked this last time so here’s another one… 

1. Me & @myriam_nicole waiting for our podium. 💕

2. Had to sleep with that thing 😂😭 leading up to these last couple of races after I had my most recent neck spasm 

3. Managed to squeeze a little date night in Lenzerheide with @kade_2000 after he got back from Audi Nines and I got back from Worlds… much needed

4. My most beautiful bike to date 💕

5. I just find @kaosseagrave stretching funny 😂

6. The ONLY food I manage to eat before a race… Literally only thought of adding chocolate at this race too! GAME CHANGER!

7. We have a riders group chat for course feedback. Any safety concerns/issues with the track get put in. Everyone agreed after day 1 practice that the last drop was a little small and we were all going sooo deep on it, this photo was sent to us to show that the chicane was changed and tightened for qualies to make the entry slower and safer 🙏🏻

8. I have a nap every. single. day at World cups. 😴😂

9. We all have a hype song before leaving for our race run… this ones mine!

10. 15 hours in to my drive home! We get 2 days at home before flying out to the US for the last World cups. X

🥈🍻!!! this one felt ✨different✨ Ain’t a win but it felt pretty darn good to be right up there with a solid run and overcome this mental block I’ve been having. It’s a work in progress but I’m so proud of the work that was put in this week from myself and my team!!! Everyone gave 110% all week. Big love @fmdracing ❤️

🎥 @gopro

Tomorrow we go hunting!!! ⚔️😤🌈
This track is truly challenging in every way, but I’m enjoying piecing the puzzle together… 🧩 📸 @maddogboris 

My run is at 12:28 UK time, you can watch it on RedBull TV and also BBC!

node.text:
A tough decision today but confident it’s the right one! I’ve been struggling with my neck ever since the slipped disk and this track is SO demanding physically and mentally. I had a great day in practice yesterday, but it was a little much for my neck and I woke up super stiff, aware that riding my bike makes it worse… I decided to sit out today. Luckily with my protected status I am able to just break the beam in Qualies which means I will still be able to race on Sunday. Trying to give myself the best chance at doing the best job possible on race day. Let’s get it. 👊🏻
📸 @svenmartinphoto

Maribor World Cup iPhone photo dump! The things you don’t always see 😆

1. Race run warm up, trying to cool down after warming up in the already extremely hot weather? 🤨
2. Proof of said extremely hot weather 🥵
3. Getting a pic of my swollen hand to show @point1athletic 
4. Keeping cool 
5.  I was reluctant about this but took it because you guys never see this side… things don’t ever really go to plan and I doubt myself enormously, like most people do!
6. The track was F#CKD 😂
7. Cuts n bruises
8. More cuts n bruises
9. Broken Van
10. Silver linings of a broken down van 🥰🥰🥰
